ns:common.topic.description:
VLISP refers to at least three distinct items.
These are, in no particular order:
A Lisp dialect implemented and formalized since 1971 at the University of Paris VIII - Vincennes, France. VLISP interpreters and compilers were designed to run on small machines and were extremely fast. This VLISP led to Le-Lisp.
A formally verified implementation of the Scheme programming language.
The "Visual Lisp" implementation included in recent versions of AutoCAD.
